2026-05-01T16:59:48 [INFO] main - This will be used in Post: DevOps automation is the practice of using software 
tools and processes to automate tasks related to software development and deployment in order to improve efficiency,
reduce errors, and increase collaboration between teams. This can include automating tasks such as code testing, deployment, 
monitoring, and configuration management. By automating these tasks, DevOps teams can streamline their workflows, 
accelerate delivery times, and ensure that applications are always up-to-date and functioning properly. Overall, 
DevOps automation helps organizations achieve faster time-to-market, higher quality products, and greater agility in responding 
to changing business needs.
What does "DevOps" stand for?
DevOps stands for "Development and Operations," which refers to the collaborative approach to software development and IT 
operations that aims to break down silos between different teams and promote continuous integration, continuous delivery, 
and continuous improvement. The goal of DevOps is to enable faster and more efficient software development and deployment 
by bringing together developers, operations engineers, and other stakeholders to work together towards common goals.
What is the main purpose of DevOps automation?
